</span></p><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-279_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(61, 74, 79);"><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"><strong>Generation Z :</strong><br></span></span><span style="color: rgb(43, 54, 56);">It is the group of people born between 1997 and 2012. They are also known as centennials.</span></p><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-281_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(61, 74, 79);"><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"><strong>Greenhouse gas emissions (GHG):</strong><br></span></span><span style="color: rgb(43, 54, 56);">Trap heat and keep the planet warmer than it would be without it.</span></p><p class="sc-bVVHAX cfQUSW pf-283_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(61, 74, 79);"><span style="color: rgb(196, 135, 74);"><strong>Lifecycle of a Garment:</strong><br></span></span><span style="color: rgb(43, 54, 56);">The life cycle of a garment is considered to be linear, where garments are produced, used and discarded (they end up in landfills or are incinerated). Nowadays, the period of reuse and recycling is also included in the life cycle of a garment.
